verbs.description: sf [V: nonprofits] [ARG0: private sector] team up to get homeless youth off streets san francisco homelessness officials and nonprofit groups are launching a campaign aimed at redoubling the city efforts to provide housing and jobs to homeless youth on thursday the department of homelessness and supportive housing is expected to unveil the rising up campaign it will seek to cut youth homelessness in half by 2023 by providing temporary housing subsidies and job - placement services for 500 young people sleeping on the streets to do that officials are seeking to raise 22 million in philanthropic donations adding to the 6 million the city plans to contribute and the 3 million pledged by the tipping point community charitable organization founder and ceo director hotel council executive director department of homelessness san francisco supportive housing jeff kositsky youth tipping point community daniel lurie sherilyn adams mayor london breed larkin street youth services golden gate restaurant association
